headline: Intuitive Surgical (ISRG) Earnings Beat Reinforces Bullish Narratives, But Valuation Stays Expensive
summary: Intuitive Surgical (ISRG) posted earnings growth of 22.5% over the past year, beating its five-year annual average of 16.2%. Net profit margins nudged higher to 28.6% from 28.5%, while annual revenue growth forecasts are set at a strong 12% compared to the broader US market’s 10.1% expectation. Despite this momentum, EPS growth is projected at 13.5% a year, trailing the US market’s 15.5% pace, and shares are trading far above an internally estimated fair value. See our full analysis for...
